South Imenti MP Kathuri Murungi has said William Ruto's running mate in 2022 should come from Mt Kenya East.
 Murungi said Meru County with over 700,000 voters and Tharaka Nithi with over 300,000 make a strong bloc to produce a presidential running mate. 
 ALSO READ:

Waiguru climbs a step up power ladder amid 2022 talk

 "There is no shortage of leaders in Mt Kenya East who can confidently take up that position," he said on Thursday.
 The legislator was speaking in his constituency during public consultations for Constituency Development Fund (CDF) projects.




